<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026-01-10-black-and-white.png" alt="wills chess problem" width="383" height="387" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-72523" srcset="https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026-01-10-black-and-white.png 383w, https://www.futilitycloset.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026-01-10-black-and-white-300x303.png 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 383px) 100vw, 383px" /></p>
<p>By W.F. Wills. White to mate in two moves.</p>

